{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17534715","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17534715"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:49:16+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:49:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15158"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15158","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15158"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.6,0.03,0.11,0.08,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7846"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109287"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7846","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7846"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15158"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91649"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4984"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"7966"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19117"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38810"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40830"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109287","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109287"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a seven-day history of high fever, severe headache, and backache, followed by a rash. He recently returned from archaeological work at a remote site in Siberia where ancient graves were being excavated. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 110/min, blood pressure 125/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 22/min, SpO2 97% on room air, and temperature 38.9\u00b0C. There is a rash consisting of deep-seated, firm, round vesicles and pustules, all at the same stage of development. The lesions are more concentrated on his face, forearms, and lower legs, with relatively fewer lesions on his trunk. The vesicles are round, tense, and feel like small ball bearings under the skin.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Smallpox","Secondary syphilis","Disseminated herpes simplex","Varicella","Molluscum contagiosum"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features highly suggestive of smallpox from the variola virus, including the characteristic prodrome of high fever and severe flu-like symptoms, followed by a synchronous eruption of deep-seated, firm vesicles and pustules involving the mucous membranes too.. It is highly contagious and transmitted via respiratory droplets via humans. The centrifugal distribution (more prominent on face and extremities) and uniform stage of lesion development are key diagnostic features. Monkeypox would present similarly and would be differentiated by pathology predominately.  \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst a tricky question as small pox has been eradicated worldwide since 1980s, it is a good differential to consider given the potential for it being used for biological attacks, and the question also requires knowledge of the other presenting rashes to rule out the other differentials. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmallpox\u003C/strong\u003E lesions appear simultaneously and progress through stages together. They are deep-seated, firm, round, and well-circumscribed. The centrifugal distribution pattern (face and extremities more affected than trunk) is characteristic. The lesions start from macules, evolve to pustules and vesicles and then will crust over during a 10 - 20 day duration. The recent exposure to ancient burial sites raises concern for exposure to preserved viral particles though it is fanciful stem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVaricella\u003C/strong\u003E typically shows lesions in different stages of development (crops) and has a centripetal distribution (more lesions on trunk than extremities). The lesions are more superficial and not as firm or well-circumscribed as smallpox lesions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESecondary syphilis\u003C/strong\u003E can present with a widespread rash but typically appears as copper-colored macules and papules rather than deep-seated vesicles. The rash is usually non-tender and may affect palms and soles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDisseminated herpes simplex\u003C/strong\u003E infection typically occurs in immunocompromised hosts and presents with grouped vesicles on an erythematous base, unlike the isolated, firm lesions seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMolluscum contagiosum\u003C/strong\u003E presents with small, flesh-colored papules with central umbilication. The lesions are typically asymptomatic and not associated with systemic symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile smallpox was declared eradicated in 1980, the possibility of exposure through archaeological work or bioterrorism means clinicians should maintain awareness of its presentation. Any suspected case should be immediately reported to public health authorities. The vaccine is still available however has many side effects and it is difficult to create a new vaccination for small pox without testing it and accidently spreading the disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Smallpox lesions appear synchronously and progress through stages together, unlike chickenpox where lesions appear in crops.","Smallpox lesions are more prominent on the face and extremities (centrifugal distribution) compared to chickenpox which is centripetal.","Deep-seated, firm, round, well-circumscribed vesicles or pustules are characteristic of smallpox."],"references":["Joel G Breman, Smallpox, The Journal of Infectious Diseases, Volume 224, Issue Supplement_4, 1 October 2021.  Available at: https://academic.oup.com/jid/article/224/Supplement_4/S379/6378097","WHO Team. Smallpox: Clincal Diagnosis.  World Health Organization. 2016.  Available at: https://www.who.int/publications/m/item/smallpox-clinical-diagnosis"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91649"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15158"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91649","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/91649"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-19T17:45:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-19T17:46:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7846"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109287"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"rela